<div class="erow">
<p>
Warning:  the functionality to allow user to add maps is new and still undergoing testing.
You are welcome to try it out, but be aware that the interface is still pretty basic, and that bugs may exist.
Please leave comments on the forum regarding any issues you have - that way they can be resolved.</p>
<h4>Georeferenced maps</h4>
<p>Georeferenced maps can be loaded onto the system with a minimum of steps</p>
<ul>
  <li>Describe the map</li>
  <li>Upload the map</li>
  <li>Optionally, crop the border off the map</li>
  <li>Click on Create</li>
</ul>
<p>Note that display of georeferenced maps during the upload process will be very slow.</p>
<h4>Plain image maps</h4>
<p>Simple scanned maps can be loaded onto the system with a few extra steps</p>
<ul>
  <li>Describe the map</li>
  <li>Upload the map</li>
  <li>Check if the map is square on the page and rotate if required</li>
  <li>Optionally, crop the border off the map</li>
  <li>Enter the projection of the map</li>
  <li>Provide the coordinates (in the grid system used by the map) for 2 known points on the map, or look them up on the topomaps</li>
  <li>Click on Create</li>
</ul>
<p>Note: maps who's projection is unknown are not supported at this time.</p>
<p>Note: you must manually click 'refresh' at the top of the left panel to check the status.  Some operations can take several minutes.</p>
<p>Note: you will have to refresh your browser (e.g. F5) after any step that changes the mapi to see those changes, namely: crop and rotate.</p>

</div>
<div class="erow">
  <%= form_for  @map, :remote=> true, :html => {:name => 'uploadform'}, :url => '/mapsheet/'+@map.id.to_s   do |f| %>
    <%= render 'shared/error_messages' %>

    Sheet Name*
    <%= f.text_field :name %>

    Series (e.g. NZMS57)
    <%= f.text_field :series %>

    Edition (e.g. Edition 1)
    <%= f.text_field :edition %>

    Scale (e.g. for 1:50k enter 50000)
    <%= f.text_field :scale %>

    Sheet number (e.g. S128)
    <%= f.text_field :sheet %>

    Published by (e.g. LINZ)
    <%= f.text_field :source %>

    Copyright notice (if required)
    <%= f.text_field :attribution %>

    Year printed* (e.g. 1945)
    <%= f.text_field :year_printed %>

    Year surveyed/revised (e.g. 1942)
    <%= f.text_field :year_revised %>

    Description
    <%= f.text_area :description %>

    <%= f.submit "Create", class: "btn btn-small btn-primary", name: "create", onclick: "linkHandler('create')", id:  "create" %>
  <% end %>
</div>
